# Main Idea + Key Details

Research consistently shows:

# Reading Comprehension

is NOT:

```text
just reading words correctly
```

It is:

```text
understanding meaning
```

Students learn:

```text
read
→ notice details
→ connect ideas
→ identify big idea
→ explain understanding
```

This develops:

* comprehension
* reasoning
* memory
* vocabulary growth
* academic reading readiness

This becomes:

# Big-Idea Thinking

Common misconceptions:

children may:

```text
pick a random detail
as the main idea
```

or believe:

```text
main idea
=
favorite fact
```

Instead:

Main idea is:

```text
what the text is mostly about
```

Details:

```text
support the main idea
```

This skill teaches:

```text
central meaning
+
supporting evidence
```

